## Remembering Things
Components need to "remember" things: current input, whether a modal is open, or a counter value. This is called **state**.

```jsx
import { useState } from 'react';

function Counter() {
  // stateVar, setterFunction = useState(initialValue)
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
      Clicked {count} times
    </button>
  );
}
```

When state changes, React re-renders the component automatically!

